net.opentsdb.query.filter

Class TagVFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.opentsdb.query.filter.TagVFilter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<TagVFilter>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TagVLiteralOrFilter, TagVNotKeyFilter, TagVNotLiteralOrFilter, TagVRegexFilter, TagVWildcardFilter

    public abstract class TagVFilter
extends Object
implements Comparable<TagVFilter>
    A base class for tag value filters that may execute against rows that come out of a scanner to determine if we should include them in the results or not. The filters should be prefixed with something to differentiate them from literal values. Every filter must be associated with a tag key. During scanning, each time a new TSUID is encountered, the map will be passed to match for matching. Plugins implementing the filter must include the following: - public static final String FILTER_NAME; A short, unique name without spaces or odd characters that is used to invoke the filter. - public static String description(); A method that returns a description of what the filter does. - public static String examples(); A method that returns a string with some examples of how to use the filter. This class also contains the list of configured filters as well as a method to load filters from plugin Jars.
    Since:
    2.2

      • match

        public abstract com.stumbleupon.async.Deferred<Boolean> match(Map<String,String> tags)
        Looks up the tag key in the given map and determines if the filter matches or not. If the tag key doesn't exist in the tag map, then the match fails.
        Parameters:
        tags - The tag map to use for looking up the value for the tagk
        Returns:
        True if the tag value matches, false if it doesn't.

      • getFilter

        public static TagVFilter getFilter(String tagk,
                                   String filter)
        Parses the tag value and determines if it's a group by, a literal or a filter.
        Parameters:
        tagk - The tag key associated with this value
        filter - The tag value, possibly a filter
        Returns:
        Null if the value was a group by or a literal, a valid filter object if it looked to be a filter.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the tag key or filter was null, empty or if the filter was malformed, e.g. a bad regular expression.

        Parameters:
        filter - The filter string to parse
        Returns:
        The filter value minus the surrounding name and parens.

      • resolveTags

        public com.stumbleupon.async.Deferred<byte[]> resolveTags(TSDB tsdb,
                                                          Set<String> literals)
        Resolves both the tagk to it's UID and a list of literal tag values to their UIDs. A filter may match a literal set (e.g. the pipe filter) in which case we can build the row key scanner with these values. Note that if "tsd.query.skip_unresolved_tagvs" is set in the config then any tag value UIDs that couldn't be found will be excluded.
        Parameters:
        tsdb - The TSDB to use for the lookup
        literals - The list of unique strings to lookup
        Returns:
        A deferred to let the caller know that the lookup was completed. The value will be the tag UID (unless it's an exception of course)
